main_text: Benefits Of MuskmelonMuskmelon is a summer fruit with a sweet taste. This fruit has high water content along with several other nutrients. The summer season demands proper hydration. Not just drinking water several fruits have also high water content which can also help in preventing dehydration. Muskmelon is also known as sweet melon. This is a refreshing fruit and many are not aware of its potential benefits. During the summer season you should consume fresh fruits on a daily basis to receive different nutrients. High water content of these fruits will also help you beat dehydration. {"1": {"comment_id": "kolekar_hospital_chembur"  "comment_text": "Aside from keeping your children indoors to avoid heatstroke  good nourishment is also important to keep them comfortable. Hereâ€™s what food items can be added to their diet:
Muskmelon - Muskmelon  like watermelon  is a fantastic summer fruit to add to your child's diet because it is high in water  electrolytes  and vitamins.

Curd - Curd  which is high in calcium  protein  vitamins  and minerals  is a tasty and healthy coolant that not only keeps your child cool but also helps them grow and fight infections.

Watermelon - Watermelon is one of the best fruits to keep your infant cool this summer because it contains 90% water  is high in antioxidants  vitamins  and electrolytes  and is low in calories.

Cucumber - Cucumber has high water content and is high in fibre and minerals  making it an ideal summer snack.

Coconut water - Tender coconut water  which is high in electrolytes (a mineral that helps the body maintain its water balance) and simple carbohydrates  is a must-have in your child's summer diet.
